<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,293,692]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,267,330,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<typeStatus box="[196,259,330,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In the general collection at 
<collectionCode box="[630,719,330,356]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8z6v-f8is" name="Saskatchewan Museum of Natural History" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">SMNH</collectionCode>
is a female pinned through the right elytron bearing the handwritten labels: “ 
<collectingCountry box="[402,484,368,394]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Persia</collectingCountry>
”, “Falderm.”, and fitting the description with 
<typeStatus box="[1045,1097,368,394]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
locality as 
<collectingCountry box="[1238,1316,368,394]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Persia</collectingCountry>
. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[318,427,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">lectotype</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus box="[506,643,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ, 
<taxonomicName authority="Boh., Gultekin" authorityName="Boh., Gultekin" box="[694,1066,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberratus">
<emphasis box="[694,882,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus aberratus</emphasis>
Boh., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[1129,1193,405,431]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2006.0">2006</number>
”, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Zoubk., Gultekin" authorityName="Zoubk., Gultekin" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubicundus">
<emphasis box="[1230,1436,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus rubicundus</emphasis>
Zoubk., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
det. 
<number box="[408,472,442,468]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2006.0">2006</number>
”. In addition, under the name “ 
<emphasis box="[835,959,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[835,956,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberratus">Aberratus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
Schh., 
<number box="[1047,1148,442,468]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="113.5" valueMax="116.0" valueMin="111.0">111–116</number>
, Bhn.” there is a male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zoubkoff" authorityName="Zoubkoff" box="[151,484,480,506]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubicundus">
<emphasis box="[151,362,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus rubicundus</emphasis>
Zoubkoff
</taxonomicName>
bearing the labels: “ 
<emphasis box="[740,903,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L: incarnates</emphasis>
, Falderm., Turcmania, Faldermann”. In the general collection of the same museum, there is another female of 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1130,517,542]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubicundus">
<emphasis box="[928,1130,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus rubicundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, placed near the 
<typeStatus box="[1328,1436,517,543]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">lectotype</typeStatus>
bearing the labels: “Sarepta”, “Becker”, “ 
<taxonomicName box="[655,836,554,579]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriplicis">
<emphasis box="[655,836,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus atriplicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Schh" authorityName="Schh" box="[880,1138,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberratus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[880,1070,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lixus aberratus</emphasis>
Schh
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1147,1215,554,580]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
”. These latter two specimens appear to have no formal 
<typeStatus box="[580,630,592,618]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
